cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computing shortest paths amid polygonal obstacles in 2D space. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes algorithms to efficiently compute shortest paths and distance queries. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with non-intersecting polygonal obstacles and their representation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as shortest path algorithms are commonly used in AI applications such as robotics and autonomous vehicles. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also relevant as the paper's algorithms can be applied to robot path planning in environments with polygonal obstacles.
